Media personality Shade Ladipo has advised Annie Idibia on how to keep her hubby’s ‘fertility’ in check permanently. Ladipo, who claimed she was only sharing her thoughts, stated 2Baba has enough kids and Annie should implore him to get a vasectomy to ensure the numbers do not increase. Vasectomy is a form of male birth control that cuts the supply of sperm to the semen.   Reactions as Julius Agwu announces return of comedy show     Osinachi’s husband should be imprisoned – Uche…     Ugandan filmmaker eyes new Africa narrative after Disney…   It’s an elective surgical procedure for male sterilisation or permanent contraception, which involves cutting and sealing the tubes to prevent sperm from entering into the urethra and thereby prevent fertilization of a female through sexual intercourse. The controversial TV presenter said her advice to Annie was based on love. “I love you Annie so now would be a great time to ask 2face to get a vasectomy. I mean, there are enough kids in the mix. #JustAThought,” she stated.